'''Odeh Burhan Shehadeh Fakhoury''' ({{langx|ar|عودة برهان شحادة الفاخوري}}; born 22 November 2005) is a [[Jordan]]ian [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Egyptian Premier League]] club [[Pyramids FC|Pyramids]] and the [[Jordan national football team|Jordan national team]].

==Club career==
===Early career===
Born in [[Amman]], Al-Fakhouri began his football career through schools and youth centers funded by [[Prince Ali bin Al Hussein]], where he was one of 8 other 6-year olds chosen to train at [[UE Cornellà]] for a short period, with the late [[Mahmoud El-Gohary]] recognizing his abilities around that time.<ref name="Al-Ghad">{{cite web |title=عودة فاخوري.. موهبة أردنية شابة بأحلام عريضة |url=https://alghad.com/Section-180/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9/%D8%B9%D9%88%D8%AF%D8%A9-%D9%81%D8%A7%D8%AE%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8A-%D9%85%D9%88%D9%87%D8%A8%D8%A9-%D8%A3%D8%B1%D8%AF%D9%86%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D8%B4%D8%A7%D8%A8%D8%A9-%D8%A8%D8%A3%D8%AD%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%85-%D8%B9%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%B6%D8%A9-1423524 |website=alghad.com |publisher=Al-Ghad |access-date=13 October 2024 |language=Arabic |date=3 October 2023}}</ref> After returning to Jordan, he joined [[Jordan Knights FC|Jordan Knights]] for 8-years. He also briefly joined [[Al-Faisaly SC (Amman)|Al-Faisaly]]. However, he described that period as unjustly, but also received awards for best player in two tournaments in Palestine and Qatar during that brief period.<ref name="Al-Ghad"/>

Since then, he became a youth product of [[Amman FC]], where he represented the club at the under-15, under-17, and under-19 levels.<ref name="Al-Ghad"/>

=== Amman FC ===
Al-Fakhouri began playing with the first team of [[Jordanian First Division League]] side [[Amman FC]] team since 2021 as a 15-year old, as he was recognized for his unique talents within the club.<ref name="Al-Ghad"/>

In a closely-fought 2–1 loss to [[Jordanian Pro League]] side [[Al-Hussein SC (Irbid)|Al-Hussein]] during the [[2023–24 Jordan FA Cup]], Al-Fakhouri found himself beating a cup record, as he became the youngest goal scorer in the cup's history at 17-years old.<ref name="alghad.com">{{cite web |title=عودة فاخوري.. موهبة أردنية شابة بأحلام عريضة |url=https://alghad.com/Section-180/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9/%D8%B9%D9%88%D8%AF%D8%A9-%D9%81%D8%A7%D8%AE%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8A-%D9%85%D9%88%D9%87%D8%A8%D8%A9-%D8%A3%D8%B1%D8%AF%D9%86%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D8%B4%D8%A7%D8%A8%D8%A9-%D8%A8%D8%A3%D8%AD%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%85-%D8%B9%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%B6%D8%A9-1423524 |website=alghad.com |publisher=Al-Ghad |access-date=12 October 2024 |language=Arabic |date=3 October 2023}}</ref>

He had received an offer from a Cypriot club during his time at Amman FC. However, he rejected the offer.<ref name="alghad.com"/>

===Al-Hussein===
On 15 August 2024, Al-Fakhouri agreed to permanently join [[Jordanian Pro League]] side [[Al-Hussein SC (Irbid)|Al-Hussein]] on a 3-year contract.<ref>{{cite web |title=الحسين إربد يظفر بهداف منتخب الشباب |url=https://www.kooora.com/?n=1348165 |website=kooora.com |publisher=Kooora |access-date=13 October 2024 |language=Arabic |date=15 August 2024}}</ref> He started with the club's B team, which participated in the [[2024 Jordanian First Division League]]. There, he was able to score three goals in the competition.

The following season, Al-Fakhouri participated in both legs of the [[2025 Jordan Super Cup]], which his club defeated [[Al-Wehdat SC|Al-Wehdat]] as a result.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Harabi |first1=Boulbaba |title=نتيجة وملخص مباراة الحسين إربد ضد الوحدات بنهائي السوبر الأردني |url=https://www.aljazeera.net/sport/liveblog/2025/7/25/al-hussein-vs-al-wehdat |website=aljazeera.net |publisher=Al-Jazeera |access-date=29 January 2026 |language=Arabic |date=25 July 2025}}</ref> On 23 August 2025, Al-Fakhouri put out a notable performance, when he scored and assisted a goal during the club's 4–1 win against [[Shabab Al-Ordon SC|Shabab Al-Ordon]].<ref>{{cite web |title=الحسين إربد يكتسح شباب الأردن برباعية ويصعد للمركز الثاني مؤقتا |url=https://royanews.tv/news/371581/%D8%B5%D9%81%D9%82%D8%A9-%D8%AA%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%84%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D8%A8%D9%8A%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AD%D8%B3%D9%8A%D9%86-%D9%88-%D8%B4%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%AF%D9%86-%D8%AA%D8%B9%D9%8A%D8%AF-%D8%AA%D8%B1%D8%AA%D9%8A%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D9%88%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%82 |website=royanews.tv |publisher=Roya News |access-date=29 January 2026 |language=Arabic |date=23 August 2025}}</ref> By the time the [[2025–26 Jordanian Pro League]] went on break, Odeh had registered 4 goals in 9 appearances.<ref>{{cite web |title=الحسين إربد يخطف النقاط الثلاث بفوز قاتل على الأهلي |url=https://www.ammonnews.net/article/957792 |website=ammonnews.net |publisher=Ammon News |access-date=29 January 2026 |language=Arabic |date=30 October 2025}}</ref> On 23 December 2025, Al-Fakhorui scored two goals during the [[2025–26 AFC Champions League Two]] campaign in Al-Hussein's 3–1 win against [[Ahal FK|Ahal]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Al Suwaifi |first1=Mohammad |title=الحسين إربد الأردني يحسم الصدارة الآسيوية أمام أهال |url=https://www.kooora.com/%D9%83%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%82%D8%AF%D9%85/%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AD%D8%B3%D9%8A%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%95%D8%B1%D8%A8%D8%AF-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%94%D8%B1%D8%AF%D9%86%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%AD%D8%B3%D9%85-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B5%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%93%D8%B3%D9%8A%D9%88%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%94%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%85-%D8%A7%D9%94%D9%87%D8%A7%D9%84/blt6e6a39ec496980b4 |website=kooora.com |publisher=Kooora |access-date=29 January 2026 |language=Arabic |date=23 December 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Hassan |first1=Fayez |title=الحسين إربد يحطّم مفاجأة آهال وينتزع الصدارة الآسيوية |url=https://www.winwin.com/%D9%83%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%82%D8%AF%D9%85/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AD%D8%B3%D9%8A%D9%86-%D8%A5%D8%B1%D8%A8%D8%AF-%D9%8A%D8%AD%D8%B7%D9%91%D9%85-%D9%85%D9%81%D8%A7%D8%AC%D8%A3%D8%A9-%D8%A2%D9%87%D8%A7%D9%84-%D9%88%D9%8A%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%B2%D8%B9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B5%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A2%D8%B3%D9%8A%D9%88%D9%8A%D8%A9 |website=winwin.com |publisher=WinWIn |access-date=29 January 2026 |language=Arabic |date=23 December 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=فاخوري ينافس البرتغالي فيلكس و8 آخرين في استفتاء الهدف الأجمل... |url=https://alghad.com/Section-180/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9/%D9%81%D8%A7%D8%AE%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D9%86%D8%A7%D9%81%D8%B3-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A8%D8%B1%D8%AA%D8%BA%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%8A-%D9%81%D9%8A%D9%84%D9%83%D8%B3-%D9%888-%D8%A2%D8%AE%D8%B1%D9%8A%D9%86-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D8%B3%D8%AA%D9%81%D8%AA%D8%A7%D8%A1-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%87%D8%AF%D9%81-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%AC%D9%85%D9%84-2061296 |website=alghad.com |publisher=Al-Ghad |access-date=29 January 2026 |language=Arabic |date=3 January 2026}}</ref>

After the success his national team achieved at the [[2025 FIFA Arab Cup]], Al-Fakhouri gained significant interest from clubs around Egypt, as well as those around Europe.<ref name=":0">{{cite web |title=عروض كثيرة على طاولة فاخوري بعد تألقه بكأس العرب... |url=https://alghad.com/Section-180/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9/%D8%B9%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B6-%D9%83%D8%AB%D9%8A%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%B7%D8%A7%D9%88%D9%84%D8%A9-%D9%81%D8%A7%D8%AE%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8A-%D8%A8%D8%B9%D8%AF-%D8%AA%D8%A3%D9%84%D9%82%D9%87-%D8%A8%D9%83%D8%A3%D8%B3-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A8-2060239 |website=alghad.com |publisher=Al-Ghad |access-date=29 January 2026 |language=Arabic |date=25 December 2025}}</ref> [[Al Ahly SC|Al Ahly]] initially showed strong interest in the player, but despite Al-Hussein accepting the fee, Al-Fakhouri feared that he wouldn't get many opportunities at the club and stalled negotiations as a result.<ref name=":0" /> [[Pyramids FC|Pyramids]] then emerged as a club interested in Al-Fakhouri's services, with an increased chance of playing at a higher level, as well as a stronger financial promise.<ref name=":0" />

Odeh bid farewell to Al-Hussein during the 4–0 win against [[Al-Jazeera SC (Amman)|Al-Jazeera]], with the posibility of moving to either Al-Ahly, Pyramids, or to Europe, with the rumoured club being from the [[Croatian Football League]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Thabet |first1=Mohammed |title=عودة الفاخوري يودع جماهير الحسين إربد قبل الانتقال إلى بيراميدز |url=https://elbaladtv.net/%D8%B9%D9%88%D8%AF%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%81%D8%A7%D8%AE%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D9%88%D8%AF%D8%B9-%D8%AC%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%87%D9%8A%D8%B1-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AD%D8%B3%D9%8A%D9%86-%D8%A5%D8%B1%D8%A8%D8%AF |website=elbaladtv.net |publisher=El-Balad TV |access-date=29 January 2026 |language=Arabic |date=24 January 2026}}</ref>

=== Pyramids ===
On 3 February 2026, Al-Fakhouri joined [[Egyptian Premier League]] club [[Pyramids FC|Pyramids]] for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite instagram |title=انتقال اللاعب عودة فاخوري إلى نادي بيراميدز المصري |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/DUNFg_ACv4G/ |postid=DUNFg_ACv4G|website=instagram.com |user=alhusseinclub |access-date=1 February 2026 |language=Arabic |date=1 February 2026}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Boateng |first1=Elias |title=Pyramids sign Jordan winger Odeh Al-Fakhouri |url=https://africasoccer.com/pyramids-sign-jordan-winger-odeh-al-fakhouri/ |website=africasoccer.com |publisher=Africa Soccer |access-date=3 February 2026 |language=English |date=3 February 2026}}</ref> On 8 February 2026, Al-Fakhouri made his debut for the club during a [[2025–26 CAF Champions League group stage#Group A|CAF Champions League]] matchup against [[Rivers United FC|Rivers United]], scoring a goal as a substitute and helping the club secure a 4–1 victory.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Solaja |first1=Kunle |title= CAF CHAMPIONS LEAGUEPyramids FC Storm Into CAF Champions League Knockout Stage, End Rivers United’s Campaign |url= https://www.sportsvillagesquare.com/2026/02/08/pyramids-fc-storm-into-caf-champions-league-knockout-stage-end-rivers-uniteds-campaign/ |website= sportsvillagesquare.com |publisher=Sports Village Square |access-date=8 February 2026 |language=English |date=8 February 2026}}</ref>

==International career==
===Youth career===
Al-Fakhouri is a youth international for Jordan, beginning his international career with the [[Jordan national under-20 football team]].<ref>{{cite web |title=إعلان قائمة المنتخب الوطني تحت 20 عاما لمواجهة سوريا واليابان وديا |url=https://www.almamlakatv.com/news/138408-%D8%A5%D8%B9%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%86-%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%A6%D9%85%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%AE%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%88%D8%B7%D9%86%D9%8A-%D8%AA%D8%AD%D8%AA-20-%D8%B9%D8%A7%D9%85%D8%A7-%D9%84%D9%85%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%AC%D9%87%D8%A9-%D8%B3%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7-%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%86-%D9%88%D8%AF%D9%8A%D8%A7 |website=almamlakatv.com |publisher=Al-Mamlaka |access-date=13 October 2024 |language=Arabic |date=17 March 2024}}</ref> During the [[2025 AFC U-20 Asian Cup qualification]] process, he found himself among the goalscorers of a 7–0 win against [[Hong Kong]].<ref>{{cite web |title=بـ 7 اهداف .. نشامى ت 20 سنة يتفوقون على هونغ كونغ |url=https://www.ammonnews.net/article/875905 |website=ammonnews.net |publisher=Ammon News |access-date=13 October 2024 |language=Arabic |date=26 September 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=المنتخب الوطني للشباب لكرة القدم يفوز على هونغ كونغ بالتصفيات الآسيوية |url=https://www.rumonline.net/print.php?id=715111 |website=rumonline.net |publisher=Rum Online |access-date=13 October 2024 |language=Arabic |date=26 September 2024}}</ref> On that period, Al-Fakhouri gained recognition as a star within the U20 national team, after showing his consistent goal-scoring prowess.<ref>{{cite web |title=الفاخوري نجم من طينة الكبار!! |url=https://www.rumonline.net/print.php?id=715334 |website=rumonline.net |publisher=Rum Online |access-date=13 October 2024 |language=Arabic |date=28 September 2024}}</ref>

On 28 August 2025, Al-Fakhouri was called up to the [[Jordan national under-23 football team]] for the [[2026 AFC U-23 Asian Cup qualification]] matches against [[Bhutan national under-23 football team|Bhutan]], [[Chinese Taipei national under-23 football team|Chinese Taipei]], and [[Turkmenistan national under-23 football team|Turkmenistan]] on 3, 6, and 9 September 2025; respectively.<ref>{{cite web |title=إعلان قائمة المنتخب الوطني ت23 للتصفيات الآسيوية|url=https://www.jfa.jo/news.php?id=30628&title=%D8%A5%D8%B9%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%86-%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%A6%D9%85%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%AE%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%88%D8%B7%D9%86%D9%8A-%D8%AA23-%D9%84%D9%84%D8%AA%D8%B5%D9%81%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A2%D8%B3%D9%8A%D9%88%D9%8A%D8%A9 |website=jfa.jo |publisher=Jordan Football Association |access-date=29 August 2025 |language=Arabic |date=29 August 2025}}</ref> He registered a total of 4 goals in 3 games.

On 23 December 2025, Al-Fakhoruri was called up to the [[2026 AFC U-23 Asian Cup]],<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hassan |first1=Fayez |title=منتخب الأردن يعلن قائمته لمعسكر قطر وكأس آسيا تحت 23 عاما |url=https://www.winwin.com/%D9%83%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%82%D8%AF%D9%85/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1/%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%AE%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%B1%D8%AF%D9%86-%D9%8A%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%86-%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%A6%D9%85%D8%AA%D9%87-%D9%84%D9%85%D8%B9%D8%B3%D9%83%D8%B1-%D9%82%D8%B7%D8%B1-%D9%88%D9%83%D8%A3%D8%B3-%D8%A2%D8%B3%D9%8A%D8%A7-%D8%AA%D8%AD%D8%AA-23-%D8%B9%D8%A7%D9%85%D8%A7 |website=winwin.com |publisher=WinWin |access-date=28 January 2026 |language=Arabic |date=23 December 2025}}</ref> participating in all four matches.

===Senior career===
On 2 October 2025, Al-Fakhouri received his first call-up to the [[Jordan national football team]] for the [[Exhibition game#International football|friendly]] matches against [[Bolivia national football team|Bolivia]] and [[Albania national football team|Albania]] on 10 and 14 October 2025; respectively.<ref>{{cite news |title=إعلان قائمة النشامى لمواجهتي بوليفيا وألبانيا وديا|url=https://www.jfa.jo/news.php?id=30705&title=%D8%A5%D8%B9%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%86-%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%A6%D9%85%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%86%D8%B4%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%89-%D9%84%D9%85%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%AC%D9%87%D8%AA%D9%8A-%D8%A8%D9%88%D9%84%D9%8A%D9%81%D9%8A%D8%A7-%D9%88%D8%A3%D9%84%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%8A%D8%A7-%D9%88%D8%AF%D9%8A%D8%A7|access-date=29 September 2025 |publisher=Jordan Football Association |date=29 September 2025}}</ref> On 22 November 2025, Al-Fakhouri was called up to the senior team once again to participate in the [[2025 FIFA Arab Cup]].<ref>{{cite news |title=إعلان قائمة النشامى للمشاركة في كأس العرب فيفا 2025|url=https://www.jfa.jo/news.php?id=30862&title=%D8%A5%D8%B9%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%86-%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%A6%D9%85%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%86%D8%B4%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%89-%D9%84%D9%84%D9%85%D8%B4%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%83%D8%A9-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D9%83%D8%A3%D8%B3-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A8-%D9%81%D9%8A%D9%81%D8%A7-2025|access-date=22 November 2025 |publisher=Jordan Football Association |date=21 November 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://fdp.fifa.org/assetspublic/ce252/pdf/SquadLists-English.pdf|title=FIFA Arab Cup Qatar 2025 Squad List|date=2025|work=FIFA}}</ref> He was regarded as [[Jamal Sellami]]'s "trump card" leading up to the tournament.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hassan |first1=Fayez |title=عودة الفاخوري "مفاجأة" منتخب الأردن في كأس العرب 2025 |url=https://www.winwin.com/%D9%83%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%82%D8%AF%D9%85/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1/%D8%B9%D9%88%D8%AF%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%81%D8%A7%D8%AE%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8A-%D9%85%D9%81%D8%A7%D8%AC%D8%A3%D8%A9-%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%AE%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%B1%D8%AF%D9%86-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D9%83%D8%A3%D8%B3-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A8-2025 |website=winwin.com |publisher=WinWin |access-date=29 January 2026 |language=Arabic |date=30 November 2025}}</ref> He participated primarily as a [[Striker (association football)|striker]] during the tournament, where he had a disallowed goal against [[Egypt national football team|Egypt]]. His role grew throughout the tournament after [[Yazan Al-Naimat]] suffered an ACL injury against [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Mokhtar |first1=Ahmed |title=من هو الفاخوري بديل النعيمات أمام الأخضر؟ |url=https://arriyadiyah.com/880550/%D9%85%D9%86-%D9%87%D9%88-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%81%D8%A7%D8%AE%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8A-%D8%A8%D8%AF%D9%8A%D9%84-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%86%D8%B9%D9%8A%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%A3%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%85-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%B6%D8%B1%D8%9F |website=arriyadiyah.com |publisher=Ar-Riyadiyah |access-date=29 January 2026 |language=Arabic |date=14 December 2025}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Despite both sharing a surname, Odeh is not related to [[Abdallah Al-Fakhouri]].<ref>{{cite web |title=كواليس السوبر_ رضا عن التحكيم .. وأبو عبيد "مسافر" .. ومعوض "وحش" وفاخوري ×2 !! |url=https://www.rumonline.net/article/742215 |website=rumonline.net |publisher=Rum Online |access-date=29 January 2026 |language=Arabic |date=27 July 2025}}</ref> Odeh is also a [[Christianity in Jordan|Jordanian Christian]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Nasser |first1=Sherbini |title=ديانة اللاعب عودة الفاخوري odeh fakhoury مسلم أم مسيحي؟ |url=https://www.elmkal.com/%D8%AF%D9%8A%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%A8-%D8%B9%D9%88%D8%AF%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%81%D8%A7%D8%AE%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8A-odeh-fakhoury-%D9%85%D8%B3%D9%84%D9%85-%D8%A3%D9%85-%D9%85/ |website=elmkal.com |publisher=Elmkal |access-date=29 January 2026 |language=Arabic |date=12 December 2025}}</ref>

==Playing style==
Al-Fakhouri's former manager João Mota described him as a player who is strong in dribbling one-on-ones against defenders, is a quick player, and is bold in the way he plays.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Suleiman |first1=Karim |title=جواو موتا: الفاخوري لاعب جريء ولم يبنٍ مسيرته بعد.. ولديه هامش التطور |url=https://www.egyptke.com/166227 |website=egyptke.com |publisher=EgyptKE |access-date=29 January 2026 |language=Arabic |date=25 January 2026}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Ashraf |first1=Israa |title=مدرب عودة الفاخوري السابق يكشف نقاط قوة وضعف اللاعبمدرب عودة الفاخوري السابق يكشف نقاط قوة وضعف اللاعب |url=https://www.elbalad.news/6847314 |website=elbalad.news |publisher=El Balad |access-date=29 January 2026 |language=Arabic |date=25 January 2026}}</ref>

